            "answer_text": "You have only two options: Work hard and fix themIgnore them and do something elseI\u2019m 18, but at around the age of 13, I\u2019ve chosen the second option. I decided not to care for school grades - after all, school grades can\u2019t feed me, right? If you want to go with the second option, it requires making a Plan B. Your parents are not going to subsidize you forever, especially since you don\u2019t \u201cstudy\u201d in school, and finding a decent job is very hard without formal education and without skills. To put it simply, you need to show your employers you will be a better candidate than \u201ceducated\u201d people. Here is my Plan B:  Learn to code Make a game, app or a website to demonstrate my skills Start a company or get a job in software developmentSo far, this plan worked flawlessly. Thanks to my disregard for school, I found many great people from many different industries who have given me job offers and helped me expand my horizons and changed the way I think. If you want to follow a similar path, you must look for alternative ways to get skills, network and make money. The path to success is long and sometimes frustrating, but it is very rewarding. ",
