            },
            "answer_text": "I\u2019m extremely perfectionist. Wich is great and awful at the same time. So I don\u2019t deal nicely with bad grades and bad results. I usually push myself as much as I can to do my very best. And when I don\u2019t do great I punish myself maybe to hard. Sometimes I put college above my family, my health (physical and psychological), my love life, my friends. And that sucks, and sometimes I don\u2019t even realize I\u2019m doing it until I blow. I\u2019ve been observing that every day, that we students have been killing ourselfs over grades. We are more depressive and suicidal than ever. THAT\u2019S NOT EVERYTHING LIFE IS ABOUT you know? I think we need to care less about theese number (or letters) affect us. A test result doesn\u2019t define you, doesn\u2019t make you a better or worst human being. It\u2019s hard to realize how much we are not gentle to ourselves, and we should. It\u2019s hard to change habits, specially in such a competive society. College and school should be PART of your life, not what all your life is about. ",
