            "answer_text": "9th grade  10th grade  11th grade  12th grade  I am currently in the 12th grade. I have failed more test this year than all my years of school combined. Ordinarily I would have been depressed and being really hard on myself because of how bad I am doing on tests. But I remember very important things: My grades do not define who I am.Me being healthy and mentally stable is more important than staying up all night studying for a test.There will be times in life where I will fail (including taking this test)Poor grades are not the end. As long as you are trying your best that is what matters. Even if you do end up failing, its okay You won\u2019t be the first. ",
