                "name": "Laurel Callahan",
                "href": "/profile/Laurel-Callahan"
            },
            "answer_text": "Let me just give you some ideas to help. Get plenty of sleep before a test. Eat properly, a well balanced meal without high fats and grease or sugary snacks. Drink lots of plain old water! At the very least a liter of water a day. Cut way back on the caffeine! Get some exercise. Walk, outside. Get lots of fresh air. When you do these things you will physically be ready to learn. Sit at the front of the class. Take lots of notes. use a highlighter to note things the teacher repeated. Ask questions and participate in class activities. Get a study buddy. Get a tutor. Talk to your teacher about extra credit work. ",
